The paper deals with the task of de-identification of patient notes in electronic health records using artificial neural networks. This task involves natural language processing and machine learning, which are typically covered in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the need for protecting patient privacy and complying with regulations such as HIPAA, which falls under the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper involves working with large datasets and optimizing performance, which are relevant to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
